Last Spring, students at MacArthur were engaged in a project called, The Ship of Tolerance. They created panels with messages of diversity and acceptance that were sewn together to create a giant sail.

The Ship of Tolerance will travel the globe but will be on display here in Chicago this week. The MacArthur Band and Chorus will perform at Navy Pier on Saturday, 9/21 starting at 2:00pm.

Ship of Tolerance NBC video: https://app.criticalmention.com/app/#clip/view/5dd1ad7f-ca7a-431f-9d15-900813c4c5c6?token=74144242-c318-447c-b842-011c77c2b7f2

post_text: This week, students all around PHSD23 are participating in the #HourOfCode2018 during Computer Science Education Week. They are enjoying coding activities without even realizing they are building problem-solving skills. One of their favorite programming activities seem to creating Minecraft adventures and directing characters in Dance Party. The Hour of Code started as an introduction to computer science, to show that anybody can learn coding basics, and to broaden participation in the field of computer science. Over 200,000 activities are registered this year from schools around the world. Go ahead take a look for yourselves. https://hourofcode.com/us #kidscancode

The Hour of Code started as an introduction to computer science, to show that anybody can learn coding basics, and to broaden participation in the field of computer science. Over 200,000 activities are registered this year from schools around the world. Go ahead take a look for yourselves. https://hourofcode.com/us #kidscancode
